**Executioner** | Townsfolk Killing
__Basics__
Whenever the Executioner is chosen to be lynched, it will be prevented, and a player chosen by the Executioner will be lynched in their place.
__Details__
The Executioner may target a player. This target can be updated once per phase, with 1 emergency change to be used whenever the Executioner wants to. Targetting a player is an immediate effect.
This player will be lynched instead of the Executioner. The Executioner may alternatively choose to not target any player. 
When the Executioner changes the lynch, their role is revealed to all, and the targeted player is lynched immediately. 
After that, the Executioner, can no longer use their ability.
